After some investigation I wrote this:
<code>import Foundation

struct Math {
   private static var seeded = false

   static func randomFractional() -&gt; CGFloat {

      if !Math.seeded {
         let time = Int(NSDate().timeIntervalSinceReferenceDate)
         srand48(time)
         Math.seeded = true
      }

      return CGFloat(drand48())
   }
}
</code>
Now you can just do <code>Math.randomFraction()</code> to get random numbers [0..1[ without having to remember seeding first. Hope this helps someone :o)
